subject: Squash (Sport)
lead_paragraph: The Trinity College men’s team extended the longest active winning streak in college sports to 202 by winning its 11th consecutive national championship. The Bantams beat host Princeton, 5-4, in the best-of-nine match. “We were like a punch-drunk fighter trying to clinch and hang on,” Coach Paul Assaiante said. “Princeton was dominating up and down the line.” Trinity has not lost since 1998.
